C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Hbl\all\LLIHandler\AnalogLLI\AnalogLLI.c
      1          /**
      2           *  @file       AnalogLLI.c
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      Module for AnalogLLI readings
      5           *
      6           *  @details    This module perform reading of Analog channels and perform some filters.
      7           *
      8           *  			Analog channels can be read as Asynchronous or on AC line peaks (at angles 90 and 270 degrees of ZC), depending
      9           *  			on which register macro used (ANALOG_LLI_ASYNCH_REGISTER or ANALOG_LLI_PEAK_REGISTER)
     10           *
     11           *  			Filters applied:
     12           *  			- Average of 2^N samples (N is a setting parameter and can change by channel)
     13           *  			- Filter reading: if a new sample is higher than 2^M points than last sample read (M is a setting parameter)
     14           *  				 average is suspended for ANALOGLLI_FILTER_SAMPLES next samples (if they are within valid range with last readings)
     15           *  			- Channel compensation: If a channel is set as "Compensated", every sample is converted using compensation
     16           *  				algorithm, depending on Reference channel defined
     17           *
     18           *              Optional Features - if SR- counterparts are defined in SRSystemConfig_prm.h and those are not, SR- values will be used as their default:
     19           *              ANALOGLLI_FILTER_SAMPLES (default 3) is debounce counter when Delta filter is enabled
     20           *              ANALOG_ONEMS_NUM_READS (default 25) set number of 1ms reading before providing each Peak to Peak / Peak values
     21           *                  if set to 0, N_Reads is used as parameter for 1ms readings - no further filters will be applied to result
     22           *              ANALOG_ONEMS_NUM_READS_DIVIDER (default 1) can be used to divide N_Reads when a new sample comes out during 1ms readings (if SRANALOG_ONEMS_NUM_READS > 0)
     23           *              ANALOG_ONEMS_FIXED_DELTA_FILTER (default 1) applies a fixed maximum/minimum Delta filter between 1ms reads.
     24           *                  If set to 0, setting file Delta parameter is used for that purpose and it will be disabled on sample result.
     25           *                  If set to 1, Delta filter on 1ms reads is disabled.
     26           *
     27           *  @section    Applicable_Documents
     28           *					List here all the applicable documents if needed. <tr>	
     29           *
     30           *  @copyright  Copyright 2015-$Date: 2015/07/24 11:27:57EDT $. Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     31           */
